            "title": "Overview",
            "level": 1,
            "blocks":
            [
                {
                    "paragraph": "Ananta control is a ticking time bomb, the deck main goal is put your opponent against the wall and force him to do desperate plays to get rid of your monsters or get out resourced. If that isn't evil enough, the deck uses the skill called Shadow Game, to burn your opponent every turn for each card on his graveyard, punishing them for doing/not doing something against your deck strategy."
                }   
            ]
